The Confederation of African Football (CAF) on Wednesday conducted the draws for the 2020 African Nations Championship (CHAN) with Nigeria drawn bye into the first round of the CAF Western Zone  B qualifiers. Three teams will qualify from the CAF Western Zone B. Nigeria will play the winner of the preliminary round between Togo and Benin Republic before booking a place in the finals billed for Ethiopia. According to the draws, Togo will host the first leg of the preliminary round with Benin Republic hosting the second. The winner of the two legged qualifier will now host Nigeria in the first leg of the last qualifying round with Nigeria hosting the second leg. The winner of this qualifier will qualify for the CHAN. In other Western Zone B qualifiers, Niger and Cote d’ Ivoire will slug it out for a ticket while Ghana and Burkina Faso will produce the third qualifier.